Well, to tell you the truth, I haven't seen much of Kareshi Kanojo no Jijou. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Just a few episodes at a local anime club.  Of course, those few episodes were enough to make me fall in love with it.<br>
<br>
And, of course, if <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.rightstuf.com">Rightstuf </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> doesn't get their butt busy and hurry up and translate it, I'll be forced to buy all the episodes on a VCD on ebay. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Classics never die<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Of course not!  Classics never die!<br>
They just get remade. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Look at all the old Magical Girl animes that have been remade!<br>
<br>
- Himitsu no Akko-chan<br>
- Mahou no Princess Minky Momo<br>
- Mahoutsukai Sally<br>
<br>
And then there are all those Gundamn remakes...<br>
<br>
Heck, I bet in maybe 10, 20 even 30 years there will be remakes of anime we all just saw just a few days ago.<br>
<br>
--<br>
